.TH "scan_pool" 9 "scan_pool" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
scan_pool \- scans a pool for changed (no longer empty PEBs).
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" scan_pool
.BI "(struct ubi_device *ubi "  ","
.BI "struct ubi_attach_info *ai "  ","
.BI "__be32 *pebs "  ","
.BI "int pool_size "  ","
.BI "unsigned long long *max_sqnum "  ","
.BI "struct list_head *free "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ubi" 12
UBI device object
.IP "ai" 12
attach info object
.IP "pebs" 12
an array of all PEB numbers in the to be scanned pool
.IP "pool_size" 12
size of the pool (number of entries in \fIpebs\fP)
.IP "max_sqnum" 12
pointer to the maximal sequence number
.IP "free" 12
list of PEBs which are most likely free (and go into \fIai->free\fP)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns 0 on success, if the pool is unusable UBI_BAD_FASTMAP is returned.
< 0 indicates an internal error.
